WEBVTT

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:17.420
This is for you, Doctor.

00:00:18.542 --> 00:00:19.860
Is it a baby croissant?

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:21.540
You want the project,

00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:23.060
but how can you make
it work like this?

00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:27.020
What you just heard
is a selected part of the full recording.

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:30.860
Nowadays, everyone knows AI can
easily fake voices to seem real.

00:00:31.020 --> 00:00:34.180
Given the current situation, I think you
should be the one listening more, Uncle,

00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:36.220
to what the coalition parties want.

00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:39.340
You need the other parties
to vote confidence in you.

00:00:39.450 --> 00:00:41.060
Then trade other ministries.

00:00:41.400 --> 00:00:43.620
On the contrary, there's nothing
more you can do.

00:00:49.010 --> 00:00:50.780
Have we really reached a dead end?

00:00:58.090 --> 00:01:00.540
Suppose if I go talk to
the coalition parties,

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:03.220
would there be any chance?

00:01:05.460 --> 00:01:07.420
That's enough for now.
If it's a dead end...

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:10.660
Thinking about it is just
wasting your energy.

00:01:12.100 --> 00:01:15.060
Tomorrow, I'll try talking to Father again.

00:01:17.020 --> 00:01:19.020
Will the result be different from today?

00:01:20.220 --> 00:01:21.140
I don't know.

00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:26.140
But if I get to talk to my father
without anyone else present,

00:01:26.650 --> 00:01:27.860
I'll tell him directly

00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:29.420
that he is making a mistake

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:32.300
by following Sun's plan.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.220
Will it work?

00:02:33.430 --> 00:02:35.660
Gel! Gel! Sis!

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:38.380
My friend updated the info,

00:02:38.440 --> 00:02:40.300
but it needs
confirmation again tomorrow.

00:02:40.890 --> 00:02:41.580
That...

00:02:41.780 --> 00:02:46.420
Our channel got the number one rating
among online news outlets!

00:02:49.220 --> 00:02:52.740
Sis, good ratings mean we can
sell ads for good prices!

00:02:53.430 --> 00:02:54.140
Mhm.

00:02:54.810 --> 00:02:57.540
Just watch out for political parties
trying to buy us out.

00:02:58.060 --> 00:03:00.620
Oh wow. You don't seem happy at all.

00:03:01.060 --> 00:03:02.220
Is something wrong?

00:03:04.460 --> 00:03:05.260
No.

00:03:05.720 --> 00:03:07.780
You can go home first.
I'll turn off the lights myself.

00:03:09.010 --> 00:03:12.540
If there's nothing else, let's all
go home, Sis. Get some rest. Yeah?

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:17.540
Maybe there is.

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:18.700
Huh?

00:03:20.010 --> 00:03:20.860
What is it?

00:03:21.450 --> 00:03:22.540
Come look at this.

00:03:28.120 --> 00:03:33.340
The PM being debated and meeting
with coalition parties isn't strange, Sis.

00:03:34.050 --> 00:03:36.140
But meeting in secret, without...

00:03:36.980 --> 00:03:41.780
Phasakorn, the coalition party leader
with the most votes?

00:03:42.780 --> 00:03:44.980
It means Mr. Wuth has a secret deal.

00:03:46.010 --> 00:03:47.700
That backstabs Phasakorn.

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:49.460
Hey, Sis!

00:03:49.930 --> 00:03:51.260
Is it about Dr. Nong?

00:03:51.890 --> 00:03:53.740
I remember you told me that

00:03:53.850 --> 00:03:56.180
Phasakorn guy
is eyeing the Doctor's seat.

00:03:56.260 --> 00:03:56.980
Right?

00:03:57.450 --> 00:03:58.580
I don't know.

00:03:59.020 --> 00:04:00.060
Haven't figured it out yet.

00:04:00.850 --> 00:04:03.420
Don't know if the deal is
to keep Dr. Nong,

00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:05.340
or to reshuffle the cabinet.

00:04:06.450 --> 00:04:08.420
Or to give Dr. Nong's seat
to a smaller party

00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:10.620
instead of For Hope Party.

00:04:13.330 --> 00:04:16.900
Who knows? This debate round
might have something fun.

00:04:19.590 --> 00:04:21.740
Surely you're not here to
persuade me to change my mind.

00:04:22.090 --> 00:04:24.300
I'd like you to hear
this matter first, Father.

00:04:24.530 --> 00:04:26.500
- So you can reconsider...
- Wait, wait.

00:04:27.730 --> 00:04:29.180
Wait for Jes to arrive first.

00:04:33.700 --> 00:04:34.580
Why?

00:04:35.220 --> 00:04:36.900
Is it such a big secret?

00:04:38.690 --> 00:04:41.100
Let him come and listen.
What's wrong?

00:04:41.760 --> 00:04:42.540
Yes.

00:04:44.980 --> 00:04:46.340
- Hello, Father.
- Ah, hello.

00:04:49.090 --> 00:04:50.820
Vee has been waiting since morning.

00:04:51.020 --> 00:04:54.940
Well, you won't give me a motorcade.
Getting around is just...

00:04:55.210 --> 00:04:57.060
so terrible from the traffic jam.

00:04:58.100 --> 00:04:59.500
Oh, sorry about that.

00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:02.620
I heard it's urgent, isn't it?
Start away.

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:09.780
I want to say that you are
being deceived by Phasakorn, Father.

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:11.740
And?

00:05:12.370 --> 00:05:14.580
Every problem that has occurred
regarding Dr. Nong

00:05:14.820 --> 00:05:16.780
has Prasakorn pulling the strings.

00:05:17.130 --> 00:05:19.220
He aims to weaken our party.

00:05:19.770 --> 00:05:23.260
And likely incited the coalition
to negotiate for better positions.

00:05:23.530 --> 00:05:25.500
And I think the information
used in the debate

00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:28.940
was also provided by him
to Nititham Party.

00:05:31.180 --> 00:05:33.020
Is Sun feeding drugs to Dr. Nong?

00:05:33.450 --> 00:05:36.460
Or did he take Dr. Nong's hand
to punch an MP in his own team too?

00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:39.340
I thought so too.

00:05:39.410 --> 00:05:41.460
Are you favoring
that Dr. Nong too much?

00:05:41.890 --> 00:05:42.660
Huh?

00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:48.740
Yes, I know the Doctor isn't perfect.

00:05:49.220 --> 00:05:52.180
But if we let him be destroyed now,

00:05:53.730 --> 00:05:55.940
after parliament dissolves
and there's a new election,

00:05:56.370 --> 00:05:58.500
we'll just have to start
all over again anyway.

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:02.900
You're not wrong.

00:06:03.210 --> 00:06:06.340
Sun is trying to bait us
into doing just that.

00:06:06.940 --> 00:06:08.420
And the timing of all these incidents

00:06:08.540 --> 00:06:10.500
coincides perfectly with
him challenging us.

00:06:10.700 --> 00:06:12.220
If it's not him planning this,

00:06:12.460 --> 00:06:13.860
then I don't know who the hell it is.

00:06:15.690 --> 00:06:17.780
Then why are you playing along
with his game, Father?

00:06:18.610 --> 00:06:20.380
I'm not exactly following him.

00:06:20.740 --> 00:06:22.070
We won't dissolve parliament,

00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:24.660
but we'll play his game
only up to a cabinet reshuffle.

00:06:24.940 --> 00:06:27.580
If we feed the coalition
until they're fat and full,

00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:28.900
give them seats to sit in,

00:06:29.260 --> 00:06:30.860
who would want
to dissolve parliament, huh?

00:06:31.020 --> 00:06:32.340
It's a waste of time making a living.

00:06:32.620 --> 00:06:35.980
And after the debate,
we won't lose much either.

00:06:36.220 --> 00:06:38.420
Because the public will only
be focused on Dr. Nong,

00:06:38.820 --> 00:06:41.020
the first minister in history

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:44.180
to be removed by a no-confidence vote.

00:06:45.980 --> 00:06:48.860
- But if we lose Dr. Nong...
- Then find a new one.

00:06:49.250 --> 00:06:50.860
There are plenty of good,
capable people.

00:06:51.770 --> 00:06:54.740
Even so, Sun will keep playing us
until we're battered.

00:06:55.090 --> 00:06:57.580
In the end, we'll still have to
dissolve parliament.

00:06:58.180 --> 00:06:59.100
No.

00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:01.460
As long as I am Prime Minister...

00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:05.700
Don't think Dr. Nong is
the only capable and good one!

00:07:07.090 --> 00:07:10.540
I just think it's not fair
to Dr. Nong at all.

00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:12.820
Not fair?

00:07:13.140 --> 00:07:14.700
It's just like back then.

00:07:14.970 --> 00:07:17.780
When Dr. Nong cut that director
from the campaign team.

00:07:18.060 --> 00:07:19.020
Do you remember?

00:07:19.330 --> 00:07:20.980
You understood it perfectly well then.

00:07:21.360 --> 00:07:23.980
So why are you acting like
you don't understand now?

00:07:29.020 --> 00:07:32.140
- Please help me.
- I really can't help you, Doctor.

00:07:32.460 --> 00:07:34.500
Mr. Wuth has given a final order.

00:07:35.260 --> 00:07:38.020
Ugh, Doctor, I'm just
a small coalition party.

00:07:38.220 --> 00:07:40.260
What leverage do I have
to negotiate with him?

00:07:41.610 --> 00:07:45.020
You should know I can't
help you with anything.

00:07:46.370 --> 00:07:48.340
Please go, Doctor. I have to go.

00:07:48.860 --> 00:07:49.820
But, Sir...

00:07:50.750 --> 00:07:53.180
From a rising star
MP to a falling minister.

00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:54.740
Many people feel sorry for him,

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:56.980
someone who worked hard
for the people.

00:07:57.110 --> 00:08:00.100
But there are also many
who are quite disappointed.

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:04.220
This time, it's unclear what,
if anything, can help Dr. Nong.

00:08:04.390 --> 00:08:05.420
(Dr. Nong Cornered?
Lobbying for Coalition Votes...)

00:08:08.180 --> 00:08:10.460
A missed delivery. For your boss.

00:08:12.210 --> 00:08:13.140
Thank you.

00:08:33.900 --> 00:08:34.860
Whose box is this?

00:08:35.230 --> 00:08:38.020
I'm not sure either.
A staff delivered it.

00:08:39.570 --> 00:08:41.380
- For me?
- Yes.

00:08:50.580 --> 00:08:52.060
- Chat.
- Yes.

00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:53.540
You can take a break.

00:08:54.250 --> 00:08:55.580
Come back in 15 minutes.

00:09:21.600 --> 00:09:23.140
Sorry to disturb you, Sir.

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:25.700
But my boss wanted me
to clarify with you.

00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:29.860
This project was finalized,
that I'd get a 30 percent kickback.

00:09:30.340 --> 00:09:31.100
Please.

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:34.060
For this phase, with the budget
you're offering, I really can't proceed.

00:09:34.170 --> 00:09:35.620
Why are you talking nonsense?

00:09:35.840 --> 00:09:38.940
- No, Sir, but I need to inform you that...
- You want the project,

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:40.660
but how can you make it work like this?

00:09:41.090 --> 00:09:42.020
Then I...

00:09:42.490 --> 00:09:45.100
might have to propose
amending the specs again.

00:09:45.740 --> 00:09:46.460
Uh-huh.

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:48.340
Then get to it.

00:09:49.050 --> 00:09:50.140
Thank you, Sir.

00:09:53.890 --> 00:09:56.500
And make sure
the amendments are seamless.

00:09:58.450 --> 00:10:01.380
If problems arise, you shouldn't
expect to keep your seat.

00:10:02.210 --> 00:10:03.620
It will be done, Sir.

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:22.140
I can't leave my position now, Sir.

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:24.060
I still have so much to do.

00:10:25.490 --> 00:10:27.740
On the contrary,
there's nothing more you can do.

00:10:31.170 --> 00:10:32.500
I can do it, Sir.

00:10:33.480 --> 00:10:34.460
I can do it.

00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:10.740
I'm begging you, Sir.

00:11:15.170 --> 00:11:16.380
Let me stay.

00:11:19.170 --> 00:11:22.220
Then you can...
order me to do anything.

00:11:24.730 --> 00:11:26.220
I'll do everything you say.

00:11:36.540 --> 00:11:37.460
I'm begging you.

00:12:09.130 --> 00:12:10.100
Sorry.

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:12.540
Did I wake you?

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:16.620
You can talk to me about anything.

00:12:18.690 --> 00:12:20.660
I've seen you looking stressed
since you got back.

00:12:26.290 --> 00:12:27.420
It's nothing.

00:12:31.780 --> 00:12:33.020
Just the debate matter.

00:12:37.410 --> 00:12:38.460
You should sleep.

00:12:40.370 --> 00:12:42.220
If you don't sleep, I won't sleep either.

00:12:44.320 --> 00:12:45.700
I'll just keep you company.

00:12:59.110 --> 00:13:00.460
Do you want to vent?

00:13:03.400 --> 00:13:04.860
It might make you feel better.

00:13:23.090 --> 00:13:24.780
You once told me

00:13:29.210 --> 00:13:31.180
that your dad isn't a good father.

00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:38.660
What about me?

00:13:42.130 --> 00:13:43.820
Am I a good boyfriend for you?

00:13:45.140 --> 00:13:46.900
Whether you succeed or fail,

00:13:47.930 --> 00:13:50.460
you are the best person in my life.

00:13:53.490 --> 00:13:55.100
No matter what anyone says,

00:13:56.420 --> 00:13:57.820
my feelings won't change.

00:14:05.290 --> 00:14:07.180
Don't overthink things anymore, okay?

00:14:13.810 --> 00:14:15.140
Can I ask you something?

00:14:19.740 --> 00:14:21.140
Suppose that...

00:14:23.170 --> 00:14:25.420
if I had to clash with your father...

00:14:28.770 --> 00:14:29.900
what would happen?

00:14:33.210 --> 00:14:35.860
That matter... is an even bigger
thought you must avoid.

00:14:40.930 --> 00:14:42.620
Let's think about how from now on

00:14:43.680 --> 00:14:46.180
we can get you back
on your feet better than this.

00:14:48.330 --> 00:14:49.660
There must be a way out.

00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:51.780
Trust me.

00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:01.100
I believe you.

00:15:05.010 --> 00:15:06.260
Don't worry, Vee.

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:11.980
I'll find a way to manage
my own thoughts.

00:15:18.290 --> 00:15:19.020
Go on.

00:15:21.050 --> 00:15:21.940
Let's sleep.

00:15:22.710 --> 00:15:24.940
If you stay up this late,
tomorrow you'll wake up

00:15:26.250 --> 00:15:27.900
with puffy eyes and an ugly face.

00:15:30.980 --> 00:15:32.020
If you can't sleep...

00:15:32.930 --> 00:15:34.060
I won't also.

00:15:38.890 --> 00:15:40.260
My baby boy.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:49.180
Go on.

00:15:50.360 --> 00:15:51.300
Let's sleep.

00:16:00.970 --> 00:16:01.780
Come on.

00:17:02.860 --> 00:17:04.380
Sorry to disturb you, Sir.

00:17:04.740 --> 00:17:06.980
But my boss wanted me
to clarify with you.

00:17:07.440 --> 00:17:10.980
This project was finalized,
that I'd get a 30 percent kickback.

00:17:11.440 --> 00:17:13.500
For this phase, with the budget
you're offering, I really can't proceed.

00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:15.060
Hey, why are you talking nons...

00:17:21.290 --> 00:17:22.740
Vee doesn't know about this, right?

00:17:26.380 --> 00:17:27.380
He doesn't know, Sir.

00:17:31.340 --> 00:17:33.660
Actually, you should have
consulted him about this.

00:17:34.420 --> 00:17:36.300
So we wouldn't have to be
in such a difficult position.

00:17:38.780 --> 00:17:40.100
Because I know

00:17:40.620 --> 00:17:41.620
that if Vee found out,

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:44.540
he would stop me.

00:17:45.850 --> 00:17:47.020
So you do know, don't you?

00:17:48.010 --> 00:17:49.420
That you shouldn't be doing this.

00:17:50.570 --> 00:17:51.700
I have no choice.

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:54.820
No.

00:17:55.940 --> 00:17:57.380
You can still stop here.

00:17:57.820 --> 00:17:58.980
Go back home.

00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:01.420
Take care of your dad and your sister.

00:18:01.670 --> 00:18:03.580
Continue your old projects
to help the villagers.

00:18:04.370 --> 00:18:06.380
I will support you in every way.

00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:07.940
Whatever legal case you face,

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:10.660
I will handle it for you, don't worry.

00:18:11.500 --> 00:18:14.980
Let's pretend you never came here
to blackmail me like this.

00:18:15.680 --> 00:18:16.580
Okay?

00:18:18.020 --> 00:18:19.780
I still have things I need to do.

00:18:21.090 --> 00:18:22.580
In my capacity as a Minister.

00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:26.820
Just let it go, Doctor.

00:18:32.930 --> 00:18:34.020
What about you, Sir?

00:18:38.850 --> 00:18:40.940
Can you let go of
the Prime Minister position?

00:18:44.100 --> 00:18:46.260
I believe the reason you're clinging
to your position now

00:18:48.490 --> 00:18:50.620
is because you have something
you need to finish.

00:18:54.450 --> 00:18:55.540
Am I right?

00:18:56.930 --> 00:18:58.140
We are not the same.

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:00.780
I'm already on the tiger's back.

00:19:01.180 --> 00:19:04.180
If I get off, I'll be mauled to death.

00:19:04.490 --> 00:19:05.700
But you are not yet.

00:19:06.200 --> 00:19:08.620
You still have a chance to
survive that you should seize first.

00:19:08.710 --> 00:19:09.660
It's alright, Sir.

00:19:11.210 --> 00:19:12.540
I'm ready to get on the tiger's back.

00:19:14.930 --> 00:19:16.140
If you make a mistake...

00:19:19.100 --> 00:19:20.220
It means death, Doctor.

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:31.780
With all due respect, Sir.

00:19:40.300 --> 00:19:41.940
I won't die alone, that's for sure.

00:19:53.090 --> 00:19:54.020
Okay.

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:57.540
If you've prepared yourself
to this extent,

00:19:58.180 --> 00:19:59.500
then I have to accept it.

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:03.420
Does this mean
you agree to help me?

00:20:04.040 --> 00:20:05.740
I can't let you go.

00:20:06.310 --> 00:20:09.500
Where can you easily find
a full-fledged politician like this?

00:20:10.300 --> 00:20:13.340
From now on,
I consider you my people.

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:16.940
I will talk to you directly,
not through Vee anymore.

00:20:20.100 --> 00:20:20.940
Agreed.

00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:22.700
Oh, one more thing.

00:20:24.090 --> 00:20:26.900
Vee absolutely must not know about
what we discussed in this room.

00:20:28.450 --> 00:20:29.420
Okay?

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:39.820
Mrs. Chonticha.

00:20:40.670 --> 00:20:42.540
Do I have any appointments
this afternoon?

00:20:42.790 --> 00:20:43.860
This afternoon, you are chairing...

00:20:44.020 --> 00:20:45.740
the strategy meeting
with the coalition parties.

00:20:46.180 --> 00:20:48.660
Then please inform the Deputy PM
to chair it in my place.

00:20:49.300 --> 00:20:50.660
I have important business.

00:20:50.920 --> 00:20:51.900
Yes, Sir.

00:20:53.340 --> 00:20:54.260
Now, Doctor.

00:20:54.640 --> 00:20:57.780
Let's discuss this grand play
of ours right away.

00:21:27.510 --> 00:21:28.460
Hello, Vee.

00:21:29.410 --> 00:21:30.580
You've lost a lot of weight.

00:21:31.050 --> 00:21:32.580
If you want to eat anything,
I'll take you.

00:21:33.850 --> 00:21:35.660
No, I just want to go home.

00:21:37.620 --> 00:21:39.660
Here, I packed your things
from the condo.

00:21:39.980 --> 00:21:41.300
But you have to stay at a new place.

00:21:41.600 --> 00:21:43.260
I rented one for you.

00:21:44.290 --> 00:21:46.860
Why not just go back to
Phu Chaloem? Why stay?

00:21:47.820 --> 00:21:48.900
Just stay for a while.

00:21:49.570 --> 00:21:51.420
I can't see the boss
anymore anyway, right?

00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:53.580
No.

00:21:54.010 --> 00:21:57.300
If you wander out now,
the other side might just take you.

00:21:59.020 --> 00:21:59.900
Sis.

00:22:00.730 --> 00:22:02.460
I'm not selling out the boss, am I?

00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:04.500
After all this?

00:22:10.250 --> 00:22:11.700
Sis, are you worried about me?

00:22:13.060 --> 00:22:14.140
Aren't you?

00:22:15.820 --> 00:22:17.500
Is it too late to object to the bail now?

00:22:18.050 --> 00:22:19.500
Let's take him back right now.

00:22:20.540 --> 00:22:22.100
Don't talk like that, Sis.

00:22:23.320 --> 00:22:25.020
Why don't you try being
in there yourself?

00:22:25.560 --> 00:22:27.380
Then you'd know what it's like.

00:22:29.540 --> 00:22:32.460
I'm sorry for making you did it.

00:22:33.390 --> 00:22:35.740
Oh, bro. Don't be so dramatic.

00:22:38.290 --> 00:22:39.580
That's just you!

00:22:41.880 --> 00:22:43.500
Even after this,
you're still not remorseful?

00:22:44.540 --> 00:22:46.460
He apologizes,
so just accept it nicely.

00:22:47.420 --> 00:22:49.700
It's not that. I mean, like...

00:22:51.850 --> 00:22:53.140
Vee doesn't need to apologize.

00:22:54.130 --> 00:22:55.980
You probably did your best, right?

00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:02.140
But from now on, you don't have to
do things like this anymore.

00:23:05.780 --> 00:23:08.300
I don't even know
what I'll do next anyway.

00:23:08.780 --> 00:23:09.940
First of all,

00:23:10.550 --> 00:23:12.420
go find a university and enroll.

00:23:13.410 --> 00:23:14.820
I'll be your guardian.

00:23:17.020 --> 00:23:18.020
No.

00:23:19.010 --> 00:23:19.780
Why?

00:23:20.100 --> 00:23:21.140
Don't want to study?

00:23:21.650 --> 00:23:23.100
I don't want a guardian.

00:23:24.860 --> 00:23:25.820
Do you get it?

00:23:27.900 --> 00:23:29.220
Take it or not?

00:23:32.240 --> 00:23:33.180
Fine, I'll take it.

00:23:47.370 --> 00:23:48.460
Is something wrong?

00:23:51.130 --> 00:23:52.340
I hope not.

00:24:06.500 --> 00:24:07.340
What is it?

00:24:10.060 --> 00:24:10.780
Hey.

00:24:11.450 --> 00:24:12.660
Even if you hate my guts,

00:24:12.980 --> 00:24:14.980
but you don't need
to be so cautious.

00:24:18.030 --> 00:24:20.900
I'm going to help Dr. Nong.
Will you listen or not?

00:24:32.130 --> 00:24:35.020
I actually agree with
what you said that day.

00:24:36.090 --> 00:24:38.460
Because I also don't want Father
to play along with Sun's game.

00:24:40.650 --> 00:24:43.540
Saving that Doctor
for the party list next time

00:24:43.730 --> 00:24:45.140
gives us a better chance.

00:24:48.500 --> 00:24:49.380
So, what's the plan?

00:24:50.020 --> 00:24:51.420
Don't be so dramatic.

00:24:52.440 --> 00:24:55.500
I probably don't need to convince you
of what's in your head, right?

00:24:56.720 --> 00:24:57.820
Just admit it.

00:24:58.260 --> 00:25:01.100
That the two of us
can think alike sometimes.

00:25:04.380 --> 00:25:05.820
It's just that your MPs...

00:25:07.210 --> 00:25:08.300
don't have enough votes.

00:25:09.240 --> 00:25:11.500
I'll talk to the coalition party MPs then.

00:25:12.090 --> 00:25:13.980
There are quite a few
who owe me favors.

00:25:15.930 --> 00:25:17.660
You might see them as small voices,

00:25:18.160 --> 00:25:19.700
but every single vote counts, man.

00:25:21.010 --> 00:25:21.980
And another thing,

00:25:23.210 --> 00:25:25.500
I've also bought off some people
in the Nititham Party.

00:25:28.340 --> 00:25:29.140
Why?

00:25:29.420 --> 00:25:31.300
Did you think you were
the only one raising cobras?

00:25:32.820 --> 00:25:33.740
What do you want?

00:25:35.680 --> 00:25:37.620
You're always so clever, aren't you?

00:25:39.260 --> 00:25:41.460
I'm certainly not helping
that Doctor for free.

00:26:00.910 --> 00:26:01.900
How's Jump?

00:26:07.090 --> 00:26:08.140
He's okay.

00:26:09.290 --> 00:26:10.340
I sent him home.

00:26:14.370 --> 00:26:15.340
Are you tired?

00:26:18.630 --> 00:26:19.380
No.

00:26:21.130 --> 00:26:21.940
Well then,

00:26:22.100 --> 00:26:23.740
are you hungry?
Want to eat something?

00:26:24.140 --> 00:26:24.980
It's alright.

00:26:26.940 --> 00:26:28.060
Take a shower first.

00:29:14.050 --> 00:29:14.900
Vee!

00:29:27.810 --> 00:29:28.660
Vee!

00:29:30.930 --> 00:29:31.860
Vee!

00:30:07.230 --> 00:30:08.500
Can you confirm once again,

00:30:08.580 --> 00:30:10.740
that all the accusations from
the opposition are untrue?

00:30:10.900 --> 00:30:13.780
- Are you being thrown under the bus?
- Doctor, can you say something?

00:30:14.010 --> 00:30:18.380
Everyone can see that Dr. Nong today
is not in his best form like before.

00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:21.420
Moreover, his strategist,
Mr. Vee, isn't by his side.

00:30:21.580 --> 00:30:24.820
Will Dr. Nong be able to handle
the opposition in today's debate?

00:30:24.980 --> 00:30:26.940
(Live: No-Confidence Debate)
The public should watch closely.

00:30:27.030 --> 00:30:28.660
Let's share your opinions in the chat.

00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:10.860
So, Doctor, let's discuss
this grand play of ours right away.

00:31:12.160 --> 00:31:14.100
Do you know why...

00:31:14.190 --> 00:31:16.940
the opposition party had to start this
no-confidence debate against us?

00:31:21.290 --> 00:31:23.300
To scrutinize
the government's performance.

00:31:24.760 --> 00:31:26.500
Then why has this country...

00:31:26.910 --> 00:31:31.300
never had a single minister removed
from office by a no-confidence vote?

00:31:33.300 --> 00:31:37.180
Don't tell me that all our past
governments have been good.

00:31:39.980 --> 00:31:42.300
It's probably because the government
always had the majority.

00:31:43.260 --> 00:31:44.140
Yes.

00:31:44.620 --> 00:31:46.020
The outcome is already known.

00:31:46.370 --> 00:31:47.740
So why even hold the debate?

00:31:50.690 --> 00:31:53.140
Because there's an audience, Doctor.

00:31:54.260 --> 00:31:58.420
The debate result isn't as scary
as the public's perception.

00:31:58.900 --> 00:32:01.220
They remember, and they talk about it.

00:32:02.260 --> 00:32:04.580
Which will affect the next election.

00:32:05.250 --> 00:32:06.100
Correct.

00:32:06.840 --> 00:32:08.280
If the social sentiment is strong,

00:32:08.320 --> 00:32:10.860
no matter how many raise their
hands in confidence on stage,

00:32:10.990 --> 00:32:13.500
backstage everyone is scrambling.

00:32:13.770 --> 00:32:16.500
Killing each other off on one side
to ensure their own survival.

00:32:16.850 --> 00:32:19.820
And if the government can't strike
a beneficial deal with the coalition,

00:32:19.950 --> 00:32:21.260
it dissolves parliament.

00:32:21.450 --> 00:32:22.460
Here comes a new election.

00:32:23.080 --> 00:32:24.700
But if the interests align,

00:32:25.500 --> 00:32:26.780
they just reshuffle the cabinet,

00:32:26.940 --> 00:32:29.220
reduce friction, and continue working.

00:32:29.650 --> 00:32:32.740
All this depends on how
strong the social sentiment is

00:32:32.850 --> 00:32:34.940
and who stands to benefit from it.

00:32:38.300 --> 00:32:39.020
So...

00:32:41.740 --> 00:32:42.900
What about this time, Sir?

00:32:44.250 --> 00:32:45.260
What will happen?

00:32:47.770 --> 00:32:49.180
The sentiment will definitely be strong.

00:32:49.730 --> 00:32:53.620
The opposition party intends
and tries to make it a social sensation.

00:32:59.250 --> 00:33:01.340
But we will make this debate

00:33:01.560 --> 00:33:04.180
a trashy drama
that frustrates the audience.

00:33:04.930 --> 00:33:08.580
It will be the most prolonged,
the most boring drama.

00:33:10.130 --> 00:33:13.740
While the opposition is debating
other ministers,

00:33:14.840 --> 00:33:17.180
there will be periodic protests.

00:33:18.180 --> 00:33:20.540
It will be about trivial,
nonsensical matters.

00:33:21.130 --> 00:33:23.140
To interrupt the debater's rhythm

00:33:23.340 --> 00:33:26.340
and prevent a smooth,
substantive debate.

00:33:27.050 --> 00:33:31.060
Which leads to the viewers at home
feeling bored because it's pointless.

00:33:34.010 --> 00:33:36.900
But for you, Doctor,
there will be a plot twist.

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:41.900
From the first draft TOR
of the telemedicine project

00:33:42.100 --> 00:33:44.580
and the actual versions
of both phases.

00:33:44.860 --> 00:33:47.140
During the time
the opposition debates you,

00:33:47.730 --> 00:33:51.300
not a single guard will
stand up to protest.

00:33:52.170 --> 00:33:55.420
Giving the opposition party the
opportunity to debate substantively

00:33:55.620 --> 00:33:57.820
and with intense content.

00:33:58.330 --> 00:34:00.380
The highlight of the entire debate
will be you, Doctor.

00:34:00.610 --> 00:34:03.980
People who turned off their TVs
will turn them back on to watch again.

00:34:04.380 --> 00:34:07.100
At first, I didn't believe it either.

00:34:07.560 --> 00:34:09.980
That we would have a minister
who is a drug addict,

00:34:10.280 --> 00:34:12.100
hallucinating, unable to control himself,

00:34:12.260 --> 00:34:13.780
and was once a murderer.

00:34:14.120 --> 00:34:15.820
But given his performance,
constantly in the news

00:34:15.900 --> 00:34:17.220
throughout the past year,

00:34:17.410 --> 00:34:19.660
once it's revealed he was high.

00:34:20.140 --> 00:34:22.820
The mystery is instantly unveiled!

00:34:23.650 --> 00:34:27.220
This time, we haven't just
caught a murderer.

00:34:27.420 --> 00:34:29.940
We've also caught a disgraced minister.

00:34:30.180 --> 00:34:32.900
Want to play the innocent one, huh?

00:34:33.880 --> 00:34:36.180
And during the time
you have to stand up and clarify,

00:34:36.420 --> 00:34:37.780
to rebut the accusations,

00:34:37.940 --> 00:34:38.940
you will stand up,

00:34:39.140 --> 00:34:41.020
but you won't be able
to defend yourself at all.

00:34:41.370 --> 00:34:43.620
So, to summarize the entire debate...

00:34:45.530 --> 00:34:47.100
I deny all of it.

00:34:48.250 --> 00:34:49.220
That's all.

00:34:49.650 --> 00:34:52.180
After the debate,
the villagers who listened

00:34:52.380 --> 00:34:55.820
will forget about all the other ministers,
except for you alone.

00:34:56.370 --> 00:34:58.660
The full force of public sentiment
will crash down on you.

00:34:59.290 --> 00:35:02.500
We will end this matter
with a cabinet reshuffle.

00:35:03.010 --> 00:35:04.420
With you remaining
in your original position.

00:35:04.660 --> 00:35:08.740
And you will become the single
most despised minister by society.

00:35:10.780 --> 00:35:12.860
I will bear the resistance
from the coalition parties.

00:35:13.620 --> 00:35:16.140
As for you, Doctor,
you'll have to work a bit harder.

00:35:16.410 --> 00:35:18.700
Because you'll have to handle
the public sentiment yourself.

00:35:20.490 --> 00:35:22.220
And you'll have to work even harder

00:35:22.420 --> 00:35:24.300
during the next election period.

00:35:25.180 --> 00:35:27.940
The real test will be when you try
to hold on to this seat.

00:35:28.210 --> 00:35:31.620
Can you create achievements
to redeem your reputation?

00:35:35.290 --> 00:35:36.380
I can do it.

00:35:42.980 --> 00:35:45.500
It can be said that this time,
the opposition dragged out every issue,

00:35:45.580 --> 00:35:47.460
almost without needing evidence.

00:35:47.620 --> 00:35:51.340
Using just one's conscience
is enough to see what is true.

00:35:51.530 --> 00:35:54.060
Most importantly is
Dr. Nong's demeanor.

00:35:54.190 --> 00:35:56.620
He looked unable to argue back,
completely out of character.

00:35:56.810 --> 00:35:59.540
From a young, new-face
politician who never gave up

00:35:59.620 --> 00:36:03.300
to a broken-winged minister
after just one year in the arena.

00:36:03.460 --> 00:36:06.060
Or is this truly the final act
for Dr. Nong?

00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:08.620
Tomorrow is the voting day.
We will find out.

00:38:15.220 --> 00:38:16.420
Next in order,

00:38:16.760 --> 00:38:18.220
I will ask the assembly:

00:38:18.810 --> 00:38:22.460
Vote of confidence or no confidence

00:38:22.850 --> 00:38:28.180
in Dr. Thanit Ponthongdee,
Minister of Public Health.

00:38:28.580 --> 00:38:31.100
Members who vote no confidence,

00:38:31.340 --> 00:38:36.260
meaning you agree with the motion,
please press the 'Agree' button.

00:38:36.570 --> 00:38:41.940
Members who vote confidence,
meaning you disagree with the motion,

00:38:42.530 --> 00:38:45.260
please press the 'Disagree' button.

00:38:45.650 --> 00:38:51.300
And members who abstain,
please press the 'Abstain' button.

00:38:51.570 --> 00:38:52.900
Please cast your votes.

00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:10.220
I'm going to help Dr. Nong.

00:39:11.210 --> 00:39:12.420
Will you listen or not?

00:39:18.640 --> 00:39:19.620
What do you want?

00:39:22.720 --> 00:39:24.620
You're always so clever, aren't you?

00:39:26.300 --> 00:39:28.380
I'm certainly not helping
that Doctor for free.

00:39:34.410 --> 00:39:36.700
Help me by resigning from the party.

00:39:40.460 --> 00:39:41.860
Stop being involved with the party.

00:39:42.380 --> 00:39:44.100
Stop being involved with that Doctor.

00:39:45.920 --> 00:39:47.460
And that Doctor gets to continue.

00:39:48.900 --> 00:39:49.820
How's that?

00:39:50.900 --> 00:39:52.580
My faction is large enough.

00:39:52.860 --> 00:39:54.460
Dad must listen to me no matter what.

00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:59.060
I'll take good care of
that Doctor, don't worry.

00:40:04.900 --> 00:40:05.740
Deal.

00:40:07.840 --> 00:40:09.660
I'll handle the paperwork right away.

00:40:11.010 --> 00:40:13.140
Oh, and another thing.

00:40:13.800 --> 00:40:16.860
I believe you won't get involved
with that Doctor.

00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:20.060
But to make sure that Doctor
doesn't get involved with you,

00:40:23.830 --> 00:40:26.020
do me a favor and cast
a surprise vote for me, will you?

00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:08.300
The assembly has passed
a vote of no confidence.

00:41:08.810 --> 00:41:10.900
170 votes.

00:41:11.220 --> 00:41:15.580
Not exceeding half of the total members
of the House of Representatives.

00:41:16.190 --> 00:41:20.380
Therefore, the assembly is deemed
to have passed a vote of confidence.

00:41:20.530 --> 00:41:23.060
It appears the entire cabinet survives!

00:41:23.180 --> 00:41:26.540
With this result, I don't know
whether to call it

00:41:26.630 --> 00:41:30.300
beyond expectations or as expected.

00:41:31.060 --> 00:41:33.660
But what the entire Thai nation
sees clearly is that

00:41:33.770 --> 00:41:36.260
no matter what evidence
the opposition presents,

00:41:36.340 --> 00:41:38.940
they cannot hold
the government accountable.

00:41:39.060 --> 00:41:40.540
Especially Dr. Nong.
(Justice Party Goes All Out, Heated Debate)

00:41:40.740 --> 00:41:42.060
(Justice Party Goes All Out, Heated Debate)

00:41:42.540 --> 00:41:43.460
Cheers.

00:41:46.250 --> 00:41:48.660
This bottle of whiskey has been
aged for twenty years.

00:41:49.300 --> 00:41:50.740
I think you'll like it, Doctor.

00:41:50.900 --> 00:41:52.300
As for me,
I can't handle it anymore.

00:41:52.540 --> 00:41:53.900
I'll just stick to wine.

00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:06.460
Thank you very much.

00:42:09.140 --> 00:42:11.700
I'm the one who should be
thanking you, Doctor.

00:42:12.440 --> 00:42:14.220
If it weren't for you,
I'd be in trouble.

00:42:18.580 --> 00:42:20.180
I checked the report.

00:42:21.340 --> 00:42:24.100
Vee really did vote
no confidence in you, Doctor.

00:42:31.340 --> 00:42:32.420
It's not surprising.

00:42:35.240 --> 00:42:37.580
He probably found out

00:42:38.580 --> 00:42:40.540
that I was talking to you
behind his back.

00:42:41.500 --> 00:42:42.660
Impossible.

00:42:42.900 --> 00:42:44.780
Only you and I
know about this matter.

00:42:44.940 --> 00:42:47.420
- That guy shouldn't know anything.
- Please, Sir.

00:42:52.690 --> 00:42:55.460
You should stop
underestimating your own son.

00:42:58.210 --> 00:43:01.140
I think Vee deserves
more recognition from you.

00:43:04.810 --> 00:43:06.500
I've already disappointed him.

00:43:09.210 --> 00:43:11.980
Don't let him have to be hurt
by his own father again.

00:43:17.640 --> 00:43:18.500
So,

00:43:19.190 --> 00:43:22.780
the two of us are... equally screwed.

00:43:31.760 --> 00:43:33.420
Vee has resigned from the party.

00:43:35.560 --> 00:43:39.180
Jes is expediting the process
for him right away.

00:43:51.770 --> 00:43:55.260
So, have you thought about
how you’re going to recover from all this?

00:43:58.430 --> 00:43:59.900
I will push for the policy

00:44:00.690 --> 00:44:02.260
to reduce doctors' working hours.

00:44:05.330 --> 00:44:07.740
I already told you that this won't work.

00:44:07.820 --> 00:44:09.820
But this time, you won't oppose me.

00:44:14.740 --> 00:44:15.820
Is that correct?

00:44:25.610 --> 00:44:26.420
Yes.

00:44:27.900 --> 00:44:30.700
I have a life-or-death matter about
Dr. Nong to discuss with you.

00:44:31.460 --> 00:44:32.500
What is it?

00:44:32.970 --> 00:44:34.060
That Dr. Nong survived

00:44:34.470 --> 00:44:35.980
wasn't because Jes went to talk.

00:44:37.080 --> 00:44:39.820
Dr. Nong blackmailed your father
with a recording of him talking

00:44:39.950 --> 00:44:41.180
to the O.P.M. rep.

00:44:41.860 --> 00:44:42.620
Huh?

00:44:43.450 --> 00:44:45.540
And now your dad has ordered
to keep Dr. Nong.

00:45:26.140 --> 00:45:27.260
Doctor, you're good.

00:45:27.820 --> 00:45:28.900
I admit it.

00:45:29.610 --> 00:45:30.660
But a bit too stubborn.

00:45:31.810 --> 00:45:33.100
Hard to work with.

00:45:42.050 --> 00:45:43.100
Are you ready?

00:45:44.130 --> 00:45:44.900
Mhm.

00:45:48.050 --> 00:45:49.340
But it's not too late to help him.

00:45:51.160 --> 00:45:54.260
I'm the only one who
can help Dr. Nong now.

00:45:55.410 --> 00:45:56.100
Oh.

00:45:57.060 --> 00:45:57.900
Wait, no.

00:45:59.250 --> 00:46:00.460
You can too.

00:46:04.490 --> 00:46:05.660
What should I do?

00:47:24.940 --> 00:47:27.620
I think you need to make
a decision quickly, Vee.

00:48:07.000 --> 00:48:07.860
Fine.

00:48:09.580 --> 00:48:10.580
I agree.

00:48:42.780 --> 00:48:44.300
So, we have a deal then.

00:48:45.300 --> 00:48:47.220
Don't you dare do anything
behind my back.

00:48:48.540 --> 00:48:49.820
I'm watching you.

00:49:08.240 --> 00:49:09.420
It's done, sir.

00:49:23.250 --> 00:49:25.620
Today, Prime Minister Khunawut
is preparing a statement

00:49:25.770 --> 00:49:26.980
to quash rumors of a party split,

00:49:27.120 --> 00:49:29.260
after narrowly surviving
the no-confidence debate.

00:49:29.460 --> 00:49:30.700
There are signs of a cabinet reshuffle,

00:49:30.820 --> 00:49:32.700
with top ministries
going to coalition partners.

00:49:32.820 --> 00:49:34.620
Most notably, there’s MP Withu,

00:49:34.720 --> 00:49:37.620
who broke the party line
during the vote, resigned,

00:49:37.770 --> 00:49:40.660
and then disappeared.
No one has been able to reach him since.

00:49:40.780 --> 00:49:43.820
The Prime Minister, as his father,
and Dr. Nong, as his close confidant,

00:49:44.010 --> 00:49:46.820
how will they respond to this?
Follow closely for updates.

00:49:50.080 --> 00:49:51.780
You want me to go out
and speak nicely,

00:49:53.130 --> 00:49:55.060
when you just ordered my execution?

00:49:58.250 --> 00:50:00.660
You know, if I didn't have to
continue working,

00:50:01.020 --> 00:50:02.340
I would have destroyed
all of you already!

00:50:02.520 --> 00:50:04.220
Hey, watch your mouth! You...

00:50:04.340 --> 00:50:05.660
Let me handle it!

00:50:05.930 --> 00:50:06.940
You stay out of it.

00:50:12.700 --> 00:50:13.780
I'm not going along with this!

00:50:15.370 --> 00:50:16.860
You can go lie to the media yourselves.

00:50:17.040 --> 00:50:17.940
You bastard!

00:50:18.000 --> 00:50:19.380
Jes, stop!

00:50:20.400 --> 00:50:21.580
Calm down.

00:50:22.460 --> 00:50:23.620
If I didn't order it,

00:50:24.660 --> 00:50:25.780
you don't stand up.

00:50:29.580 --> 00:50:30.500
Doctor.

00:50:31.770 --> 00:50:33.660
Right now, we need to
maintain appearances.

00:50:34.420 --> 00:50:37.540
Otherwise,
our government won't last long.

00:50:39.520 --> 00:50:40.780
And you, Doctor,

00:50:42.570 --> 00:50:44.340
won't be able to continue your work.

00:50:45.410 --> 00:50:47.980
I’m not standing next to you
while you trash Vee in front of the press.

00:50:48.180 --> 00:50:49.660
Then what do I say about a son

00:50:49.750 --> 00:50:51.420
who abandoned his father
and his party?

00:50:51.500 --> 00:50:52.820
Then just tell them!

00:50:53.330 --> 00:50:54.700
That his father is an asshole!

00:50:54.980 --> 00:50:55.740
You bastard!

00:50:55.810 --> 00:50:57.220
- Jes, enough!
- Hey!

00:50:58.690 --> 00:50:59.580
You know what?

00:51:00.120 --> 00:51:02.900
Even if I curse your ancestors to hell,

00:51:04.290 --> 00:51:05.900
your father can't do anything to me.

00:51:07.570 --> 00:51:10.020
Because your father knows that
if anything happens to me now,

00:51:10.730 --> 00:51:11.940
he's definitely finished.

00:51:13.000 --> 00:51:14.860
You’re the only idiot in this room
who doesn’t get that,

00:51:15.950 --> 00:51:17.220
Because you're stupid.

00:51:17.690 --> 00:51:19.420
Stop clinging to your father
and leeching off him.

00:51:25.700 --> 00:51:27.460
Whenever you're done venting, Doctor,

00:51:28.570 --> 00:51:29.980
let's put our heads together

00:51:31.050 --> 00:51:33.620
and figure out what
we're going to tell the public.

00:51:50.580 --> 00:51:51.620
Damn it.

00:52:17.020 --> 00:52:20.020
What’s your response to MP Withu’s
no-confidence vote against you?

00:52:20.260 --> 00:52:22.620
It's nothing, really. It's his right.

00:52:23.220 --> 00:52:25.220
He's just exercising
his constitutional right.

00:52:32.110 --> 00:52:34.540
But MP Withu is said to be closest to you.

00:52:34.840 --> 00:52:37.300
How do you feel about his vote?

00:52:37.980 --> 00:52:40.340
Honestly, it’s not a matter of feelings.

00:52:41.580 --> 00:52:44.500
I trust he voted on his own reasons,

00:52:44.630 --> 00:52:45.980
not emotions.

00:52:46.220 --> 00:52:49.100
Let's just say, if anyone reaches him,
please get his explanation.

00:52:49.260 --> 00:52:50.740
I’m interested in it too.

00:53:01.020 --> 00:53:03.740
Losing such an important advisor like this,
what will you do going forward?

00:53:03.970 --> 00:53:05.060
It's nothing, really.

00:53:05.340 --> 00:53:07.300
I'll just continue working.

00:53:12.010 --> 00:53:14.660
Have you made any attempt
to contact MP Withu?

00:53:15.250 --> 00:53:16.220
That's right.

00:53:16.500 --> 00:53:17.460
Not at all.

00:53:18.700 --> 00:53:21.060
Right now,
I'll just focus on my work.

00:53:38.460 --> 00:53:40.300
- Are you still there?
- Yes, Sir.

00:53:58.360 --> 00:53:59.340
From now on,

00:53:59.810 --> 00:54:01.540
I'll have to be even more careful.

00:54:16.890 --> 00:54:18.060
How are you?

00:54:21.140 --> 00:54:22.300
Please don’t do that again.

00:54:26.240 --> 00:54:28.020
It’ll look like we planned to meet.

00:54:30.220 --> 00:54:31.180
I don't care.

00:54:31.660 --> 00:54:32.580
You should.

00:54:35.000 --> 00:54:36.500
You still have a lot to do.

00:54:37.850 --> 00:54:38.860
And so do I.

00:54:45.410 --> 00:54:47.100
Aren’t you going to tell me anything?

00:54:53.900 --> 00:54:54.980
I’m fine.

00:54:56.250 --> 00:54:57.260
No need to worry.

00:55:00.370 --> 00:55:01.780
It's not like that, Vee.

00:55:06.290 --> 00:55:09.540
How do I get us back to how we were?

00:55:12.900 --> 00:55:14.380
Can you tell me, Vee?

00:55:20.340 --> 00:55:21.340
No matter what,

00:55:21.970 --> 00:55:23.900
we can't go back
to how we were anymore.

00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:30.020
I'm sorry for what I did
to your father, Vee.

00:55:30.820 --> 00:55:31.700
Okay.

00:55:33.330 --> 00:55:36.060
Is there anything else
you hold against me?

00:55:36.380 --> 00:55:37.340
No, there isn't.

00:55:40.570 --> 00:55:42.540
I know I messed up, Vee.

00:55:45.650 --> 00:55:47.500
I ruined everything myself.

00:55:51.610 --> 00:55:53.060
But can you come back?

00:55:53.850 --> 00:55:55.660
Can you trust me one more time?

00:55:58.340 --> 00:56:00.100
We don't even have to work together.

00:56:02.890 --> 00:56:06.260
I just want you to be by my side
like before, that's enough.

00:56:09.650 --> 00:56:11.100
We're past that point.

00:56:14.380 --> 00:56:16.220
If there's nothing else, I should go.

00:56:25.730 --> 00:56:26.860
I'm begging you, Vee.

00:56:31.370 --> 00:56:33.060
Give me one last chance.

00:56:35.840 --> 00:56:37.820
I won't let you down again.

00:56:38.620 --> 00:56:39.620
I'm begging you.

00:56:42.460 --> 00:56:43.300
Don't.

00:56:44.820 --> 00:56:47.220
I... don't want it anymore.

00:56:57.160 --> 00:56:58.780
Can I ask you one more thing?

00:57:06.090 --> 00:57:07.100
That night...

00:57:09.700 --> 00:57:10.900
when I survived...

00:57:16.050 --> 00:57:18.260
was it because you saved me?

00:57:23.900 --> 00:57:25.260
Why would I help you?

00:57:38.970 --> 00:57:39.860
That's true.

00:57:42.220 --> 00:57:43.180
Goodbye.

00:59:07.860 --> 00:59:09.420
So you've decided to face the media?

00:59:09.880 --> 00:59:10.860
Not exactly.

00:59:11.810 --> 00:59:13.260
Let's be direct then.

00:59:19.540 --> 00:59:20.860
I want to ask you

00:59:21.610 --> 00:59:23.020
to join the Wiwat Siam Party.

00:59:23.900 --> 00:59:24.900
Wow.

00:59:26.240 --> 00:59:28.940
This move...is unexpected.

00:59:30.170 --> 00:59:31.980
I thought you'd come to ask
about the secret clip.

00:59:42.450 --> 00:59:43.860
Sorry to disturb you, Sir.

00:59:44.250 --> 00:59:46.420
But my boss wanted me
to clarify with you.

00:59:46.780 --> 00:59:48.060
smiling like that...

00:59:48.530 --> 00:59:51.020
might make people think you quit
because you hate your father.

00:59:51.930 --> 00:59:52.860
No, it won't.

00:59:54.970 --> 00:59:57.060
I just think the timing is too perfect.

00:59:58.370 --> 01:00:00.900
It coincides with my father's order
to get rid of Dr. Nong.

01:00:02.770 --> 01:00:04.820
And he used the final
minutes of his life...

01:00:05.370 --> 01:00:06.540
to send this clip to you.

01:00:14.970 --> 01:00:16.260
This Doctor is something else.

01:00:17.540 --> 01:00:20.220
I told you, that's why I like him.

01:00:22.280 --> 01:00:23.660
But not that kind of like.

01:00:24.340 --> 01:00:25.260
Don't get the wrong idea.

01:00:27.580 --> 01:00:30.180
All the more reason I know
I choose the right person.

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:35.300
I want you to help the Doctor.

01:00:37.450 --> 01:00:39.140
Take over Wiwat Siam for me.

01:00:47.500 --> 01:00:48.780
You already know

01:00:49.210 --> 01:00:50.420
that the place we're in

01:00:50.960 --> 01:00:53.900
is full of cheaters,
people seeking their own gain.

01:00:54.850 --> 01:00:57.260
But we can still change
this fucked-up game together.

01:00:58.530 --> 01:01:00.660
I want you to take over
Wiwat Siam Party.

01:01:03.610 --> 01:01:04.980
Everything I sent you

01:01:05.910 --> 01:01:08.740
is information I've gathered
since I started working for the party.

01:01:09.690 --> 01:01:11.540
I hope it will be of some use to you.

01:01:25.460 --> 01:01:26.620
You're very bold.

01:01:27.490 --> 01:01:28.860
To invite me into politics.

01:01:29.770 --> 01:01:31.060
Even people more difficult than you...

01:01:31.970 --> 01:01:33.260
I've recruited them all.

01:01:35.020 --> 01:01:36.260
But I still believe

01:01:37.290 --> 01:01:40.300
that Dr. Nong is the person
who can truly change politics.

01:01:43.890 --> 01:01:45.740
If politics doesn't change him first.

01:01:49.490 --> 01:01:51.500
So you want me to be
your watchdog, is that it?

01:01:54.940 --> 01:01:56.580
A journalist who bites
and doesn't let go.

01:01:57.420 --> 01:01:59.420
The kind you can't buy off
no matter what.

01:02:00.390 --> 01:02:03.580
If I had to guess your motivation,
there are only two possibilities.

01:02:04.330 --> 01:02:06.420
If it's not to get revenge on politicians,

01:02:08.480 --> 01:02:10.820
then you must truly want
to see this country change.

01:02:13.890 --> 01:02:16.060
I don't need to tell you
my personal reasons.

01:02:24.820 --> 01:02:26.540
You don't need to tell me.

01:02:28.130 --> 01:02:29.620
Because no matter which one it is,

01:02:30.810 --> 01:02:31.740
Dr. Nong...

01:02:32.270 --> 01:02:34.660
is the person who can help
you achieve both.

01:02:36.650 --> 01:02:39.060
Your instinct tells you
that too, doesn't it?

01:02:41.850 --> 01:02:43.580
Do you trust him that much?

01:02:46.410 --> 01:02:49.940
For some people, even if I know
they shouldn't be trusted...

01:02:51.850 --> 01:02:53.140
but he already has my heart.

01:02:57.340 --> 01:02:58.740
I have faith in you.

01:03:00.770 --> 01:03:02.460
From the first day we met

01:03:04.160 --> 01:03:05.220
until now.

01:03:32.570 --> 01:03:34.420
And I will come back to you.

01:03:41.300 --> 01:03:43.140
(I love you always)

01:03:57.760 --> 01:03:58.900
I love you.

01:05:25.340 --> 01:05:27.540
Thank you for keeping your word.

01:05:30.980 --> 01:05:34.500
Welcome to the Puea Khwam Wang Party.

01:05:49.220 --> 01:05:50.180
I promise,

01:05:50.970 --> 01:05:52.740
I won’t let you down.